    "title": "You Shall Not Use Grace as a Sword, By Which You Attempt to Slay The Moral Law",
    "date": "2/15/08",
    "from": "From YahuShua HaMashiach, Our Lord and Savior",
    "spoken": "The Word of The Lord Spoken to Timothy",
    "forLine": "For All Those Who Have Ears to Hear",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "para",
        "segments": [
          {
            "t": "bold-italic",
            "v": "Thus says The Lord:"
          },
          {
            "t": "text",
            "v": "Say no more,"
          },
          {
            "t": "italic",
            "v": "“Grace versus The Law.”"
          },
          {
            "t": "text",
            "v": "Say rather,"
          },
          {
            "t": "italic",
            "v": "“Grace AND The Law.”"
          },
          {
            "t": "text",
            "v": "For Grace is the fulfillment of The Law. And where there is an absence of grace, there is lawlessness. Therefore, keeping The Law is a reflection of My own spirit in you. For anyone who says,"
          },
          {
            "t": "italic",
            "v": "“I am in The Lord and He is in Me,”"
          },
          {
            "t": "text",
            "v": "while forsaking The Law, is a liar, and will be found as such in the Day of Reckoning. For I AM WHO I AM, the same and unchanging, nor do I stand divided against Myself. Yet My children do continually use My name and that gift given them as a sword by which they attempt to justify their sins, which I hate! Desecration!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "poetry",
        "lines": [
          [
            {
              "t": "italic",
              "v": "Thus until the Day be fulfilled,"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "t": "italic",
              "v": "Let those who do wickedly continue therein,"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "t": "italic",
              "v": "And let those who seek righteousness walk therein,"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "t": "italic",
              "v": "Until the harvest is complete..."
            }
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "poetry",
        "lines": [
          [
            {
              "t": "italic",
              "v": "But oh how blessed are those who have"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "t": "italic",
              "v": "Received of Grace, and seek to please The Father"
            }
          ],
          [
            {
              "t": "italic",
              "v": "By obeying His Law, and teach men so..."
            }
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "poetry",
        "lines": [
          [
            {
              "t": "italic",
              "v": "Grace AND The Law."
            }
          ]
        ]
      }
    ],
